    "# FP mining for precision-focused follow-up (VLST)\n",
    "\n",
    "**Goal:** mine **false positives** on the **test** split using the **same deploy probabilities as `advanced.ipynb` §9** (`p_cal_winner` / `p_test_winner`). That matches **`win_name`** chosen there via **`ENSEMBLE_DEPLOY`** (default **`max_pr_cal_pool`** → argmax **PR-AUC on calibration** among `pool_pr_cal` variants). The export snippet stores **`deploy_selection`** so this notebook can print the rule next to **`win_name`**.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Inputs:** After **`advanced.ipynb` §9**, run **`code/modeling/snippets/fp_mining_export_cell.py`**. It writes **`fp_mining_bundle.joblib`**, **`deploy_winner_arrays.npz`**, **`deploy_winner_meta.json`**, **`kaggle_fp_inputs_manifest.json`**, **`README_FP_INPUTS.txt`**.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Multi-run:** Set **`VLST_FP_RUN_TAG`** (e.g. `run03_of_10`) so outputs go under a subfolder and do not overwrite when you repeat **`advanced`** + FP mining.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Kaggle:** Section 1 looks for exports under **`/kaggle/working/vlst_fp_inputs`**, then common **`/kaggle/input/...`** layouts (including **nested** folders). If the sidebar shows a long path such as **`/kaggle/input/datasets/<user>/<slug>/vlst_fp_inputs`**, that is valid — section 1 also **recursively** searches under **`/kaggle/input`** for `fp_mining_bundle.joblib` (or the NPZ+meta pair). Override with **`VLST_FP_INPUT_ROOT`** only if needed.\n",
    "\n",
    "Set env vars only if auto-detect fails — in a **cell before** section 1, point to the directory that **directly** contains `fp_mining_bundle.joblib` (or the NPZ+JSON pair):\n",
    "\n",
    "```python\n",
    "import os\n",
